tes\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"a live version\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"The Feast\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2185}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gods\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"Jan Harmensz Biljert\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would explain the guy in blue body paint with fruit covering up his junk - he was portraying Dionysus, the god of wine and theater.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2323, \"end\": 2331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.334446331655899e-25, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guy\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"blue body paint\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"fruit\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"his junk\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2301}, {\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"theater\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics left us with that image, at least: The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.#Paris2024#OpeningCeremonypic.twitter.com/FBlQNNUmvV It's nearly impossible to find a video of the opening ceremony now, even on the official Olympics YouTube channel.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2437, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9993554565041597, \"rank\": 0.00034886995250697994, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begi